The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                 NATION BRIEFS
                              
	 New Delhi, Aug. 2 (PTI): The Supreme Court has held that if a man and a woman have been living together for a long time and been accepted by society as husband and wife, the relationship can be presumed to be a valid marriage.           
	The two-judge bench said that in disputes over the validity of a marriage, courts can draw a presumption on the basis of the conduct of the two parties.                   
	 Shimla (PTI): Himachal Pradesh has become the 10th state to achieve the Centres two-child-per-couple target for population control. The state has achieved a fertility rate of two or less children per woman before the deadline of 2010.                   
	 Srinagar (PTI): Six youths have been arrested in Kupwara district while allegedly attempting to enter Pakistan-occupied Kashmir for arms training. The men are from Baramulla district, senior superintendent of police, Kupwara, Uttam Chand said. This is the first arrest for attempting to cross over this year, he said.                   
	 Dehra Dun (PTI): A Class XII student has allegedly committed suicide in Dehra Dun after his parents scolded him for not concentrating on his studies.                                                                                                                           
